<subSubSection id="68AA6541B85FFFACFF6207A7CED5FE68" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="200F36CAB85FFFACFF6207A7CED5FE68" blockId="6.[151,1436,228,486]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">
Although monophyly of this section was highly supported in analyses conducted by 
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85FFFACFB7307A7C834FF70" author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[1158,1385,228,254]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85FFFACFB2307A7C84FFF73" box="[1238,1298,228,253]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85FFFACFF620649CCCBFEAA" author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[151,406,266,292]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85FFFACFEF60649CC63FEAD" box="[259,318,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
, its relationship with other sections in clade D (Figure 
<quantity id="E7489B2FB85FFFACFBEC0649C91AFEAA" box="[1049,1095,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85FFFACFBBB0649C846FEAA" author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[1102,1307,266,292]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85FFFACFB680649C985FEAD" box="[1181,1240,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) is unclear because they form a polytomy. Since the morphological differences between species belonging to 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85FFFACFAB10672C800FEC4" box="[1348,1373,305,330]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85FFFACFF62061BCDA2FEFF" box="[151,255,344,369]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Minimae</emphasis>
are not great, its current rank is probably not appropriate, and it should be merged with other sections in clade D and be reduced to a taxon of lower rank. A &quot;shortly branched inflorescence with alternate phyllotaxis&quot;, as described by 
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85FFFACFE0406E6CFACFE31" author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[497,753,421,447]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85FFFACFDAB06E6CFC4FE30" box="[606,665,421,446]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
, and a flattened basal leaf (
<bibRefCitation id="44214B3BB85FFFACFBC706E6C85FFE31" author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[1074,1282,421,447]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85FFFACFB7606E6C9E3FE30" box="[1155,1214,421,446]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) are putative synapomorphies of sect. 
<emphasis id="12C4EAD8B85FFFACFE4F068FCF7FFE6B" box="[442,546,460,485]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Minimae</emphasis>
, which is not recognised here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
